
From _Asian_Paleo_, by ChihYu Chiang, ISBN 9781682682616, pg 37
35 to 40 minutes total

1 lb chicken, thinly sliced
salt, pepper, garlic powder, thyme
1 large shallot (or scallions), thinly sliced
4 or 5 garlic cloves
1/2 cup coconut milk
3 Tbsp chicken stock
5 oz shitake

Preheat oven to 400°F
Season chicken with salt, pepper, garlic, thyme.
Sear chicken with ghee over medium high heat.
Transfer chicken to a medium sized casserole (9 inch baking dish).
Sauté shallot and garlic in ghee (add a little salt).
Layer the shallot and garlic over the chicken.
Add coconut milk and chicken stock.
Spread mushrooms over the top.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Increase heat to 425°F, bake another 5 to 8 minutes.
